{"ticker": "TEM", "company": "Tempus AI", "weight_sum": 19.580000000000002, "etfs": ["ARKUX", "ARKSX", "ARKVX", "ARKG", "ARKK"], "is_private": false, "query": "($TEM OR \"Tempus AI\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since_time:1778048643 until_time:1778062654", "n_fetched": 2, "n_kept": 2, "n_dropped": 0, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2051886412518105463", "url": "https://x.com/AretardInvestor/status/2051886412518105463", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/AretardInvestor/status/2051886412518105463", "text": "$TEM \nJust to rub more salt in the wound:\n\n44% growth YoY for insights (AI)...\n\n126% NRR = Each client is spending 26% more money each year...\n\nThe most 'comprehesive' bear thesis I've seen on $TEM cites that:\n'Tempus is just a diagnosis company with a better UI that makes it look like it's AI...'\n\nThat bear thesis doesn't make sense, I'll explain the following:\nAs an AI company wholy owning your data source is what in business we call vertical integration, they don't exclusively depend on 3rd parties to provide the data, they gather it themselves...\nIt's a flywheel that compounds with time.\n\nWhile it's true Dx currently 'pays' the bills, that misses the point completely, they use the data from their Dx to build a better, more complex and stronger dataset that ultimately will eventually surpass their Dx revenue.\n\nFrom my POV, anyone invested in $TEM for the long run owns a future 'royalty' on patient diagnosis.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 2, "replyCount": 0, "likeCount": 15, "quoteCount": 1, "viewCount": 951, "createdAt": "Wed May 06 04:46:57 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 5, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2051886412518105463", "displayTextRange": [0, 276], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "AretardInvestor", "url": "https://x.com/AretardInvestor", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/AretardInvestor", "id": "1927477640442630144", "n